Env: MacBook Pro (13-inch, Intel Core i5, macOS Monterey 12.4)

* Install postgresql or other SQL System
- install brew with command:
    brew install postgresql
- start postgresql with command:
    brew services start postgresql
- run psql (default user) with command:
    psql postgres

* Change password for user postgres
- change password with command:
    alter user postgres with password '888';

* Create Data Base store
- create DB with command:
    create database goods;
- leave psql with command:
    \q

* Create table products with columns (id, name, price)
- switch to goods DB with command:
    psql -d goods
- create table products with given columns with command:
    create table products(id serial primary key, name varchar(30) unique, price float);
- check created table with command:
    \d
- check columns in table products with command:
    \d products

* Create table orders with columns (id, product_id, quantity)
- create table orders with given columns with command:
    create table orders(id int, product_id int, quantity int, constraint fk_product_id foreign key (product_id) references products(id));
- check created table with command:
    \d
- check columns in table orders with command:
    \d orders

* Add 5 different values to products
- add values to products table with command:
    insert into products(name, price) values ('Apple', 10.99), ('Orange', 30.99), ('Watermelon', 50), ('Banana', 29), ('Strawberry', 89.99);
- check added values with command:
    select * from products;

* Add 5 different values to orders according to your products
- add values to orders table with command:
    insert into orders(product_id, quantity) values (1, 300), (2, 400), (3, 800), (4, 300), (5, 200);
- check added values with command:
    select * from orders;

* Create select with the result with such columns (name, price, quantity, total)
select p.name, p.price, o.quantity, total(p.price * o.quantity) from products as p join orders as o on p.id = o.product_id;


